   {:e #blake3 "4d0b81cd94135ecc5a1795bcd2a1028049d1e92ee0704d9a39236f114a3cfd71" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Connection dynamics (UAQ-DYNAMICS) and witness suggestions (UAQ-WITNESS) need comprehensive testing. UNIT TESTS for connection_weight: (1) Fresh connection (no activations) returns 0.5 (uninformative prior). (2) Connection with 8 confirms, 2 rejects → confidence ~0.71 (Laplace smoothing=2). (3) Connection activated 5 sessions ago → temporal decay 0.9^5 = 0.59 of confidence. (4) Connection with source entity changed since last activation → accelerated decay 0.7^sessions. (5) Hebbian boost 2.0 → effective_weight = confidence * decay * 3.0. (6) Zero calibration events → confidence 0.5 (prior). UNIT TESTS for update_connection_hebbian: (7) Same-command proximity adds 1.0 to hebbian_boost. (8) Same-session adds 0.5. (9) Multiple co-activations accumulate. UNIT TESTS for decay_session_connections: (10) All hebbian_boost values halved. (11) Connections with zero boost unchanged. PROPTEST: (12) For random (confirms, rejects, sessions_stale, hebbian_boost): effective_weight >= 0. (13) More confirms → higher effective_weight (monotonic in confirmation ratio). (14) More stale sessions → lower effective_weight (monotonic in staleness). (15) Higher hebbian_boost → higher effective_weight. UNIT TESTS for witness suggestion: (16) Store with unwitnessed INV and matching test → suggestion block appears. (17) Store with all INVs witnessed → no suggestion block. (18) After braid witness confirm → INV no longer in completeness gaps. (19) Suggestion novelty decays across repeated status calls. E2E: (20) scripts/e2e_connection_dynamics.sh — init store, create INVs, add tests, run status, verify suggestion appears, run witness confirm, verify coverage improved, run status again, verify different suggestion. Each check: [PASS]/[FAIL] with timing and diagnostic data. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Log connection entity, confidence, decay, hebbian, effective_weight for every assertion. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/tests/connection_dynamics.rs + scripts/e2e_connection_dynamics.sh" :op :assert}
